rComments: PROS: He knows his stuffs and seems to try to make the lectures more attractive. CONS: Wrong problem set solutions, lab PCs that are 10+ years old and constantly failing (and only supports USB 2.0), etc. He doesn't like to answer student questions or acknowledge he made typos/mistakes.

Professor Liebeherr is one of the best professor I have had in undergrad. ECE461 is a very practical and in depth networking course. The labs teach you a lot, and the virtual labs introduced this year were quite a bit of fun. Very clear instructions. If you'r career will have anything to do with Software and IT, take his course.
Never seen anyone so excited to talk about boring networks stuff. Doesnt mean you would understand anything tho.
He is a good professor. He is passionate about the subject and explained the concepts well.

Gave me a lot of attitude when I asked him a question about one of the problems on the quiz. Before then I thought he was a decent prof. That incident completely changed my mind and I have no respect for this guy now.

A truly dedicated professor who actually cares about the students' progress. It's a shame that a lot of students don't take him more seriously. Networks II was a unique and enjoyable course that anyone with an interest in the field should sign up for.

Provides excellent support via his course website, with the complete set of lecture notes, quiz solutions, and problem sets with solutions. Lectures are a bit lacking in hands-on examples, but overall he is a good professor.
